subSubSection.paragraph:
Description:—
Valve neither straight nor arcuate, but slightly curved toward the apices (more pronounced in the longer specimens) and the raphe branches near the center at 4–6º to one another; lacking a stauros (
Figs 50–53
). Dimensions in the 
Yap
population length 228–247 µm, width 5.0 µm inflated to 8.3 µm at center and 7.6 µm at apex; Bikar Atoll specimens 124–145 µm long, width 3.9 /5.8 / 5.1 µm (
Figs 52–54
). Striae consistently 
19 in
10 µm, mostly parallel but radiating at center, convergent at apices. Areolae circular/quadrate to transapically rectangular, becoming transapically elongate in several striae near the central area (
Figs 54–59
); one row of areolae larger along each side of the raphe. Central area scarcely broader than sternum (
Fig. 55
). Raphe straight, not deflected at center (
Figs 51, 52, 55
). Raphe externally overlapped by irregular silica flap (
Figs 55, 56
), internally bordered by ribs that are continuous except at the central area (
Figs 54, 57–60
). No evidence for craticular bars.
